  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Marketing Executive",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a dynamic and results-driven <strong>Marketing Sales Executive</strong> to join our team. This role offers a competitive <strong>base salary plus commission</strong>, rewarding you for both consistency and performance.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Client Acquisition &amp; Lead Generation:</strong></u></p>\n<p>Identify potential clients and industries that need marketing services. Develop outreach strategies (networking, LinkedIn, cold calls, referrals). Manage and grow the sales pipeline.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Relationship Management:</strong></u></p>\n<p>Build and maintain long-term client relationships. Act as the main point of contact between clients and the agency. Ensure client satisfaction and upsell/cross-sell additional services.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Sales Strategy &amp; Targets:</strong></u></p>\n<p>Develop sales strategies aligned with company goals. Achieve monthly/quarterly revenue targets.</p>\n<p>Track performance metrics (conversion rates, revenue growth, lead quality).</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Proposal &amp; Pitching:</strong></u></p>\n<p>Prepare tailored proposals, quotations, and presentations. Conduct sales pitches and communicate the agency’s value proposition effectively. Negotiate pricing and contract terms.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Collaboration with Internal Teams:</strong></u></p>\n<p>Work closely with marketing to align client expectations. Provide feedback to the team based on client needs. Ensure smooth handover from sales to account management.</p>",
